<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1374,1723]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">
The genus was revised by 
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen" box="[446,649,1374,1399]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Andersen, N. M. (1982 b) Semiterrestrial water striders of the genera Eotrechus Kirkaldy and Chimarrhometra Bianchi (Insecta, Hemiptera, Gerridae). Steenstrupia, 9, 1 - 25." type="journal article" year="1982" yearSuffix="b">
Andersen (
<number box="[568,626,1374,1399]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="1982.0">1982</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
and seven species were recognized. More recently, eight more species were described from 
<collectingCountry box="[398,458,1410,1435]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[473,543,1410,1435]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">China</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[608,703,1410,1435]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Tran" box="[720,943,1410,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Yang, C. M. (2006) New species of the water strider genera Eotrechus Kirkaldy and Rhyacobates Esaki (Heteroptera: Gerridae) from Vietnam. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 54, 11 - 20." type="journal article" year="2006">
Tran &amp; Yang 
<number box="[884,943,1410,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tran" box="[958,1186,1410,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Tran, A. D. &amp; Zettel, H. (2006) Notes on Eotrechus Kirkaldy, 1902 (Heteroptera: Gerridae), with descriptions of two new species. Zootaxa, 1353, 39 - 51." type="journal article" year="2006">
Tran &amp; Zettel 
<number box="[1127,1186,1410,1435]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Vitheepradit" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Vitheepradit, A. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2007) A review of Eotrechus Kirkaldy (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Thailand with descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 1478, 1 - 19." type="journal article" year="2007">
Vitheepradit &amp; Sites 
<number box="[151,210,1447,1471]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus" box="[221,462,1446,1471]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Polhemus, J. T., Tran, A. D. &amp; Polhemus, D. A. (2009) The genus Eotrechus (Heteroptera: Gerridae) in Vietnam, with descriptions of two new species. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, 57, 29 - 37." type="journal article" year="2009">
Polhemus et al. 
<number box="[401,462,1447,1471]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). This genus is distributed from 
<collectingCountry box="[826,884,1446,1471]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">India</collectingCountry>
eastward to 
<collectingCountry box="[1027,1122,1446,1471]" name="Vietnam" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and is found on the vertical rock faces of waterfalls. More specifically, members of this genus in 
<collectingCountry box="[976,1076,1482,1507]" name="Thailand" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Thailand</collectingCountry>
seemed to occur closer to the margins of waterfalls, where the rocks were dampened by occasional splashing. Six species are known from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,253,1554,1579]" name="Thailand" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, which is the most diverse fauna compared to that of other Southeast Asian countries. Most members of this genus in 
<collectingCountry box="[326,426,1590,1615]" name="Thailand" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Thailand</collectingCountry>
are local endemics and restricted to certain mountains, with the exception of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Eotrechus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hygropetricus">
<emphasis box="[1412,1429,1591,1614]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">E</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,306,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">hygropetricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is found in several of the western mountain ranges (
<bibRefCitation author="Vitheepradit" box="[980,1280,1626,1651]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Vitheepradit, A. &amp; Sites, R. W. (2007) A review of Eotrechus Kirkaldy (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Gerridae) of Thailand with descriptions of three new species. Zootaxa, 1478, 1 - 19." type="journal article" year="2007">
Vitheepradit &amp; Sites 
<number box="[1219,1280,1627,1651]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Members of this genus were found only at elevations of 
<quantity box="[675,821,1662,1687]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.74" metricValueMax="13.8" metricValueMin="5.68" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" unit="m" value="974.0" valueMax="1380.0" valueMin="568.0">568–1380 m</quantity>
and usually with 
<taxonomicName box="[1038,1283,1662,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Onychotrechus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="esakii">
<emphasis box="[1038,1283,1662,1687]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="58">Onychotrechus esakii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on wet rock surfaces at waterfalls (
<bibRefCitation author="Vitheepradit" box="[402,610,1698,1723]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" refString="Vitheepradit, A. (2008) The semiaquatic Heteroptera (Gerromorpha) of Thailand: Faunistics, Biogeography, and Phylogeography. Ph. D. Dissertation, University of Missouri, Columbia, Missouri, USA. [total page number not cited]" type="book" year="2008">
Vitheepradit 
<number box="[549,610,1699,1723]" pageId="11" pageNumber="58" value="2008.0">2008</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
